50|$|In 1893 {{he earned}} his medical {{doctorate}} at Leipzig, and was later director of the neurological department of St. Georg Hospital in Hamburg. He designed the Trömner <b>reflex</b> <b>hammer,</b> a popular <b>reflex</b> <b>hammer</b> that is used for evoking cutaneous and myotatic responses.|$|E
