5000|$|The Taylor or {{tomahawk}} <b>reflex</b> <b>hammer</b> {{was designed}} by John Madison Taylor in 1888 [...] and is the most well known <b>reflex</b> <b>hammer</b> in the USA. It consists of a triangular rubber component which {{is attached to a}} flat metallic handle. The traditional Taylor hammer is significantly lighter in weight when compared to the heavier European hammers.|$|E
